commentTextItems.html: finishes it off in style flicking the leg side ball well over long leg

commentPostTextItems.html: A well deserved win for Bangladesh to level the series 1-1 even though they aloowed Zimbabwe to recover from 47/6. The bowling again was good but today the batsmen applied themselves a lot better to reach the target comfortably on a pitch that was not tailor made for batting. The surface did improve later in the day, but it was the way the batsmen applied themselves that saw them to the win.
So the series is level and all to play for on Friday, please join us again for that.

commentTextItems.html: decides he has had enough, goes down on one knee and lofts the slower ball one bounce over midwicket
line and length all defensive
short outside off, gently chops straight at gully
defends back down the pitch, not taking any chances
still getting slight reverse as he is defended back down the pitch

commentTextItems.html: gets well forward outside off, thick edge gets a run to third man
slides that down the leg side, flicked away to fine leg
slower ball, shortish, but enough confidence to stroke that on the up to the off
touch straight and full, pushes from the front foot towards midwicket
line and length gets him well forward with a solid defence to the off
outside off driving, that came back a bit, gets the inside edge, Taibu standing up has no chance

commentPostTextItems.html: Rainsford with 2 overs left now has a last chance

commentTextItems.html: another slow ball from the back of the hand is defended to the off
full on the legs, shuffles inside that and clips it neatly to deep midwicket for his 50
just on the off, short of length, defends back to the off side
slow ball from the back of the hand is defended to the off
starts with a very slow ball, forward defence to point
flighted up and that ends his spell as well
